# ⚠️  BACKUP FILE — DO NOT RENAME BACK TO .npmrc without reading below
# =====================================================================
# This was the old registry override pointing to localhost:4873 (Verdaccio).
# 
# ❌ PROBLEM: This made npm/yarn try to download ALL packages from your
#    local Verdaccio instance instead of the real npm registry.
# 
# ✅ SOLUTION: The project now uses the default npm registry directly:
#    https://registry.npmjs.org/
#
# 🔧 If you truly need Verdaccio, use scoped registry ONLY for your packages:
#    @montezuma:registry=http://localhost:4873/
#    (Without the global `registry=http://localhost:4873/` line)
# =====================================================================
